contentrichtext.text: [[Image:Map gelderland wisch.jpg|right|thumb|Wisch in Gelderland]] '''Wisch''' is a former municipality in the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] province of [[Gelderland]]. The municipality was created in 1818, in a merger of [[Terborg]] and [[Varsseveld]], and existed until 2005, when it became a part of the new municipality of [[Oude IJsselstreek]].<ref>Ad van der Meer and Onno Boonstra, "Repertorium van Nederlandse gemeenten", KNAW, 2006. [http://www.knaw.nl/cfdata/publicaties/detail.cfm?boeken__ordernr=20061061]</ref> Besides the villages of Terborg and Varsseveld, the municipalities also covered the villages and hamlets [[Bontebrug]], [[Heelweg-Oost]], [[Heelweg-West]], [[Silvolde]], [[Sinderen]], and [[Westendorp]]. ==References== <references/> {{coord|51|56|N|6|19|E|region:NL_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki|display=title}} [[Category:Populated places in Gelderland]] [[Category:Former municipalities of Gelderland]] {{Gelderland-geo-stub}}
